				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Updelta\hbox{pH},$$\end{document} researchers have sought to measure the lumen pH and determine the pKas of key proteins and enzymes. These downstream responses to the pH trigger have been investigated by a combination of measuring the lumen pH and correlating it to the amount of qE. The effect of ΔpH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Updelta\hbox{pH}$$\end{document} on qE has been quantified by fitting the relationship between observed qE quenching and measured lumen pH to various equations, as in Takizawa et al. (2007), Johnson and Ruban (2011), and Johnson et al. (2012). Several experimental methods have been developed to measure the lumen pH as well as the ΔpH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
